narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a lot about Hadrian and the Roman empire during his reign. I also learned how to think critically and analytically about artwork in general.

It was a bit daunting in the beginning to take on a research project that would last the whole semester and would be the main focus of the course. But I found the presentations very helpful for preparing me to write the paper and they helped improve my public speaking. This class also forced me to think on my feet whether we were analyzing a single monument or trying to draw connections between multiple works.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The structure of the course was pretty free form. I think this worked well with our group, but some people might like a little bit more structured discussion.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would recommend this course to someone interested in this time period or who was interested in Roman art in general.
Yes, it was a really collaborative environment. Professor Kleiner is always available to help and gives really great feedback. Don't be afraid to take this if you are an undergrad.
